Manila Not to Replace Negotiator for Hostage Release The Philippine government said Saturday that it will not replace Nur Misuari as its chief negotiator for the release of 21 hostages held by the Muslim extremist group Abu Sayyaf.
The Abu Sayyaf group, reckoned to number no more than 500, is the most violent rebel group in the Philippines.Philippine Group Threatens to Kill Hostages The Philippine Muslim extremist group Abu Sayyaf has threatened to behead some of the 21 hostages they abducted last Sunday in Malaysia because they do not want to talk with a government negotiator.
